article.headline: Prairie View 49, Southern 47
article.story: PRAIRIE VIEW, Texas (AP) -- Jason Breckenridge scored the game-winning basket with two seconds remaining to lift Prairie View A&M to a 49-47 win over Southern University on Saturday night. The game-winner was Breckenridge's only basket in shooting 1-of-11 from the floor. He also grabbed six rebounds and had two assists. Anthony Oha led Prairie View (5-22, 5-13 Southwestern Athletic Conference) with 13 points on 5-of-6 shooting from the field. He also went 3-for-5 from the free-throw line. Chris Alexander had 10 points and grabbed seven rebounds for Southern (13-14, 10-8). Deon Saunders and Nicholas Egland added nine points each. Prairie View scored 12 points off 22 Southern turnovers.
